    h1 Range Slider Vue Component
    ul.docs-index
    p Range Slider Vue component represents <a href="../docs/range-slider.html">Range Slider</a> component.
    h2 Range Slider Components
    p There are following components included:
    ul
      li <code><b>f7-range</b></code>
    h2 Range Slider Properties
    table.params-table
      thead
        tr
          th Prop
          th Type
          th Default
          th Description
      tbody
        tr
          th(colspan="4") &lt;f7-range&gt; properties
        tr
          td init
          td boolean
          td true
          td Initializes Range Slider
        tr
          td value
          td number<br>array<br>string
          td
          td Range Slider value, must be array in case of dual range slider
        tr
          td min
          td number<br>string
          td
          td Minimum value
        tr
          td max
          td number<br>string
          td
          td Maximum value
        tr
          td step
          td number<br>string
          td 1
          td Maximum value
        tr
          td label
          td boolean
          td false
          td Enables additional label around range slider knob
        tr
          td dual
          td boolean
          td false
          td Enables dual range slider
        tr
          td vertical
          td boolean
          td false
          td Enables vertical range slider
        tr
          td vertical-reversed
          td boolean
          td false
          td Makes vertical range slider reversed. (Only when #[code vertical:true])
        tr
          td draggable-bar
          td boolean
          td true
          td When enabled it is also possible to interact with range slider (change value) on range bar click and swipe.
        tr
          td format-label
          td function(<span>value</span>)
          td
          td Method must return formatted range knob label text. As an argument it receives label value
        tr
          td scale
          td boolean
          td false
          td Enables range slider scale
        tr
          td scale-steps
          td number
          td 5
          td Number of scale steps
        tr
          td scale-sub-steps
          td number
          td 0
          td Number of scale sub steps (each step will be divided by this value)
        tr
          td format-scale-label
          td function (<span>value</span>)
          td
          td Method must return formatted scale value. As an argument it receives currect scale step value. This method will be called as for each scale step.
        tr
          td limit-knob-position
          td boolean
          td
          td Limits knob position to the size of the range bar. By default enabled from iOS theme
        tr
          td disabled
          td boolean
          td false
          td Defines whether the range slider is disabled or not
        tr
          td id
          td string
          td
          td Range slider element ID attribute
        tr
          td input
          td boolean
          td false
          td If enabled, then it will render <code>input type="range"</code> element inside as well
        tr
          td input-id
          td string
          td
          td Input element ID attribute
        tr
          td name
          td string
          td
          td Input element "name" attribute

    h2 Range Slider Events
    table.events-table
      thead
        tr
          th Event
          th Description
      tbody
        tr
          th(colspan="2") &lt;f7-range&gt; events
        tr
          td range:change
          td Event will be triggered when Range Slider value has been changed
        tr
          td range:changed
          td Event will be triggered on slider knob release after value change
    h2 Range Slider Methods
    table.methods-table
      thead
        tr
          th Event
          th Description
      tbody
        tr
          th(colspan="2") &lt;f7-range&gt; methods
        tr
          td .setValue(<span>newValue</span>)
          td Set new range slider value
        tr
          td .getValue()
          td Returns range slider value
